<br>
Wary, and fully alert, Hermes slowly walked up the trail that led to the base of the Tree.  Something was definitely wrong.  The Tree Hag should have already made her appearance.  No once could approach the Tree without first encountering its guardian.<br>
<br>
Hermes now more scared than ever, quickly scanned the area.  Nothing.  No sign of her at all.  As he was about to turn around and head to another part of the Tree, he noticed a scorch mark upon the grass.  Inspecting closer, he realized there were actually quite a lot of them.  It looked like tiny hoof marks, in fact hundreds of them, all running in varying directions.  <br>
<br>
What could they be?  And as Hermes pondered, something large dropped down from above.<br>
