<br>
&quot;Lord Apollo, your altar is ready.&quot; Tepshet said bowing and slipping into the darkness. He nodded to himself and walked through the temple to a large altar used for making prophecies. He sat down, picking up the Prophet herbs and rubbed them across his nose, inhaling deeply. Insense burned in the background. Apollo steadied his train of thought and closed his eyes. In a flash he was somewhere else.<br>
<br>
******<br>
<br>
Mortals ran mindlessly though the streets. Mothers abandoning daughters, father their sons. The sky seemed to bleed, the clouds float black the sky rain blood. There was light, but there was no sun. Yet there was a sun and a moon, who chased each other insanely through the sky.<br>
<br>
The sea, foamed and bubbled crashing against the rocks of Africa. Against the cliffs of Ithica. Tidal waves over came whole towns. Athens itself was under the boiling sea. Apollo saw his uncle Poseidon struggling to calm the oceans to no avail.<br>
<br>
Purple and midnight blue smoke whipped through the empty air. Loud moans, the moans of restless souls, lost souls, storming through the Underworld. Tartarus itself was crumbling upon itself. The river Styx overflowed onto its shores. Loud banging, very loud. As souls banged on the doors of Hades palace. He held the doors himself trying to stop the souls. No use, the souls banged down the doors, trampling Hades and pushing around Persephone who screamed Hades name in vain.<br>
<br>
His very sister Artemis, runs through the forest, all the animals who once loved her, chasing her, their eyes cold and lifeless. The trees uprooted themselves falling in her path. Bushes shed their berries, and rocks shattered.<br>
<br>
Dionysus gasped for air as the grape vine wound tighter around his throat. The grip kept growing tighter as the forest itself seemed to be attacking him. The wolves ran up and started to nibble at his flesh, the panthers too, clawed at his skin.<br>
<br>
Zeus, sat upon his throne howling commands at the gods. Hera stood next to him, crying. Zeus hurled his thunderbolts at the beasts and enemies that scaled Olympus. Then there he stood, an entity of so much evil, it shook Apollo in his seat, who was already seizing, his priests trying to help him. The entity was dressed in all black, his face unseen. Zeus and the entity began to grapple, fighting each other. Zeus was out weighted, and was beat with a blow to the back of the head.<br>
<br>
The entity laughed holding the universe in his palm. He stood out in no where, creating around him a universe of chaos. He continued to laugh as he began to crush the universe. And that was it, the once proud Zeus would inevitabally fall, and the evil entity would rule all!<br>
********<br>
<br>
Apollo snapped out of his tranze and dismissed the priests.<br>
<br>
&quot;I must talk to Hermes.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uividionysusivi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IVIDionysusIVI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/2/01 12:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Clouds of Inspiratiom</span><hr size=1> Dionysus was sitting pleasently on His Ivory Throne wrapped in the Vine as he Wrote his new Drama For the Local Amphitheater. He stared out the window next to him looking for inspiration as he often does from the forest sorrounding Thebes , but this time something differant arose.<br>
 <br>
Being a God of revelry he could feel in his gut mortal and divine feelings of anguish and terror for that is how he new when to make people happy threw these feelings. But this time he felt it ten tmes worse then ever. It was coming from up North and he wondered is His Norse friends were alright but the thought was dismissed after he realized his own safety may be in jeopardy. <br>
<br>
After putting down his quill pen he walked towards the window his arms behinds his back the two temple gaurds stood strongly on either side of him. He Stared out the window facing Northward almost seeing a black cloud in the distance. He thought to himself to pay a visit to his brother Hermes but first he should rally up troops.<br>
<br>
In a large effort with his advisors he made a large army situates in Thebes and now was the time he though to visit his brother before he is to late to help. Thats when he disappeared , Appearing beside Hermes.<br>
<br>
