<br>
::This is crazy.  I can't be injured from suffocation.  I don't even need to breathe!  But I am about to black out.  I've got to do something fast.<br>
<br>
Within the gelatinous mass, Hermes transformed himself into an odd form comprised of massive spikes.  Yet the gel entity still Hermes fast.  And so Hermes desperate, began to swell in mass.  Inch by inch, volume upon volume, Hermes enlarged himself.  It was very hard to do, for the gel increased its contraction upon the godling.<br>
<br>
But something was happening, the gel had turned from a maroon red to a hazy orange.  And slowly, the spikes began to poke through.  As soon as one spike had punctured the gel, Hermes immediately turned himself into a hot spray, and quickly shot out of the creature.<br>
<br>
Shifting back into his humanoid form, Hermes began gasping for breath.  But the gel wasted no time in pressing on in the attack.  It suddenly became a flying scimitar, weaving and slicing through the air, as if it was being swung by an invisible arms-master.<br>
<br>
Hermes was too tired from before.  Somehow this creature had managed to sap a large quanitity of Hermes immortal stamina.  So all that the messenger of the gods could do was dodge.  He ducked underneath a decapitating swing, and lunged to the left.  He knew without looking that the blade would not be far behind.  <br>
<br>
::I've got to try something quick.  There's no way I can keep this up for long.  <br>
<br>
And suddenly it dawned on him.  He was in the realm of the Tree of Time.  Therefore why not let the Tree handle this.<br>
<br>
And so Hermes maneuvered himself until he was standing right in front of tree, and facing the oncoming blade.  At the least possible moment, Hermes somersalted over the scimitar and landed safely away.  But the blade, being carried by its momentum, kept going forward.  And suddenly it had stabbed the Tree and become enbeded.<br>
<br>
The Tree is a sentient being, although immobile, it carried within it a vast storage of knowledge and power.  It was already grieving for its lost guardian and companion, and so the Tree wasted no time in seeking revenge.  <br>
<br>
The blade tried desperately to release itself, but the sap from the Tree, caused from the stab wound, had already seeped onto the scimitar.  As more and more clung to the blade, the blade tried all the harder to free itself.  With deseperation, the blade changed back into its native form; a creature with three miniscule horns, a pig snout, and auburn fur all over its body.  It's left arm was stuck in the tree, and was already covered by sap.  <br>
<br>
The demon was desperate and suddenly it changed its right arm into another blade.  Realizing what was about to happen, Hermes shot out a blast of intense cold upon the creature.  Now with its right arm frozen, and its left arm immoblized, the demon's fate was sealed.<br>
<br>
Hermes cracked an evil smile.  ::There's no way you can escape now, so struggling is futile.  But you might as well keep trying.  The Tree is going to take its own sweet time in enveloping and digesting you.  And I am guessing that you probable had something to do with the Tree Hag's disappearance, I'm sure you're going to feel every painful moment.  And since I have your undivided attention, there are a couple of questions I would like you to answer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=madmartigan>Madmartigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/2/01 5:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.planetkilmer.com/valbum/wil-13.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tavern songs</span><hr size=1> ::Madmartigan leads the way to his favorite tavern in waygarth, the Green Dragon. He walkes up to the bartender and puts down three gold pieces::<br>
